A Component Library is the code side of theÂ Design Kit. 

It's a list of `reusable components` the *developers use* to create new experiences.

Like theÂ Design Kit, the Component Library uses theÂ Design TokensÂ for a consistent design signature that is easy to maintain.

## **Content Design**

The Content Design is meant to be used by everyone - writers or non-writers.

Content Design defines voice, tone and glossary, but also rules and recommendations for writing in an inclusive and consistent manner.

It is likeÂ [Design Kit](https://backlight.dev/mastery/what-is-a-design-system#design-kit)Â for the words and have a tremendous impact on the experience of the user.